description: The tally comes as Azerbaijan details for the first time its losses in the six-week war with Armenia.
title: Nagorno-Karabakh conflict killed 5,000 soldiers
title_page: Nagorno-Karabakh conflict killed 5,000 soldiers - BBC News
maintext: The war broke out between the two former Soviet republics in late September. The two countries had never resolved the territorial dispute over Nagorno-Karabakh, which is part of Azerbaijan but under the control of neighbouring Armenia.
